FBIS4-8040 "dreeu069_y_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Federal Churkin: `New Situation Created' by Attack Churkin: `New Situation Created' by Attack LD1004213694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 2110 GMT 10 Apr 94 LD1004213694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Serbo-Croatian BFN [Excerpts] Belgrade, 10 Apr (TANJUG) -- Vitaliy Churkin, Russian President Yeltsin's special envoy for Yugoslavia and Russian deputy foreign minister, arrived in Belgrade this evening. Upon his arrival, Churkin said that a new situation has been created after the attack launched by NATO planes on Serb positions near Gorazde. The Russian president's special envoy stressed that he would be in contact with Moscow during the night. Churkin is expected to meet Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic tomorrow. [passage omitted] It has been learned that Churkin is planning to visit Zagreb and Sarajevo where he is expected to meet Croatian and Muslim officials.
